    <h4><b> Our Impact – How are we helping to end malnutrition?</b> </h4>
    <ul class='circles'>
      <li>In Zambia, the SUN CSA used media campaigns and convinced MPs to form an All Party Parliamentary Caucus on food and nutrition. Nutrition was also included in manifestos and political commitments. This has been replicated by alliances in Malawi, Tanzania and Kenya as a direct result of the experience sharing with Zambia.</li>
      <br>
      <li>The Peru CSA persuaded Government to include conditions in cash transfer programs for poorest, requiring mothers to take children for medical checks. This led to a 40% drop in child malnutrition in targeted areas.</li>
      <br>
      <li>In Laos, Civil society was not well coordinated before the SUN Civil Society Alliance began work in 2014. Civil Society now has strong, credible partnership with Government and local civil society have platform for participation. The CSA helped run the first ever National Nutrition Forum for all sectors, all levels of government, civil society </li>
